description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a motivated individual to join the Oxford AHSN team in a new and exciting position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with stakeholders from across the health and social care sector in the Oxford AHSN region, you will be supported by the Director of Patient Safety and Clinical Improvement and the Senior Programme Manager for Mental Health and function as part of the Patient Safety and Clinical Improvement team. You will have a good understanding of the healthcare system, quality improvement methodology, the adoption and spread of innovations, and Mental Health and healthcare. Clinical experience in a Mental Health speciality will be an advantage but is not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will demonstrate:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Ability to be creative, dedicated and passionate about improvement projects relating to mental health;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Outstanding programme/project management skills, leadership and expertise;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Strong interpersonal skills;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Be skilled in building credibility and strong relationships across the health and care system;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Have excellent verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job description and person specification are an outline of the tasks, responsibilities and outcomes required for the role. The post holder will carry out any other duties as may reasonably be required by their line manager to fulfil the objectives of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Term:&lt;/strong&gt; FTC 18 months or secondment opportunity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; The post holder will be based at the AHSN Office, Magdalen Centre, The Whitehead Building, Oxford Science Park. However, the post holder will be required to travel throughout the AHSN area (Oxfordshire, Berkshire, Buckinghamshire and Milton Keynes), and occasionally to other locations in England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKatherine EdwardsEmail addresskatherine.edwards@oxfordahsn.org&lt;/p&gt;
